kb:currents-phase-2
    rdfs:label "F29.2 — Fetch: n8n Currents Monitor + browser fallback" ;
    pred:depends-on kb:currents-phase-1 ;
    pred:description "n8n workflow (extends the Source Monitor pattern): scheduled polling of RSS/Atom feeds and watched pages every 30 minutes respecting each current's cadenceMinutes, dedupes items by URL into a data table, app syncs down and pushes arrivals through the type gate. Direct browser fetch fallback (fetchCurrentDirect) for CORS-friendly feeds, with a clear CORS-flavoured error otherwise. Ranking: BGE-small embedding affinity between item text and the graph's top-degree entities; near-duplicate collapse via cosine clustering; content-policy filter drops blocked items pre-rank. SHIPPED 2026-07-03: n8n workflow qb9uPZ8GScAmuUOX (Reckons Currents Monitor) live-tested against https://hnrss.org/frontpage — real items fetched, deduped, and served back via webhook. App side: src/lib/integrations/n8n/currents-sync.ts (registerCurrent, fetchCurrentItems, fetchCurrentDirect, processArrivals — builds the article node only, skips full extraction on the unattended sweep since it's too heavy; deeper extraction stays a manual, on-demand step from the review UI), src/lib/rdf/current-ranking.ts (rankItems, topEntityLabels). settings.n8nBaseUrl added (reused by both F20 cloud sync and F29.2). 26 unit tests (RSS/Atom fixtures, mocked embeddings, mocked fetch, mocked addStatements)." ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Phase> ;
    pred:part-of kb:currents ;
    pred:has-status "functional" ;
    pred:has-workflow kb:n8n-currents-monitor .

kb:currents
    pred:relates-to kb:content-safety ;
    pred:has-phase kb:currents-phase-3 ;
    pred:depends-on kb:local-offload ;
    pred:principle "Add, merge, and review are the base spine — currents never bypass them. Personalization data (location, interests) stays local-first; the VPS only fetches public feeds." ;
    pred:description "Recurring external content streams (currents) that merge into a graph through the existing add/merge/review spine. Each arrival becomes pending facts: a document/article node plus extracted concept nodes with provenance links. Personalization is the graph itself: headlines ranked by embedding affinity to the graph's entities. The pod is a graph view mode where pending arrivals render translucent and drifting until accepted. Ground News has no official public API (verified 2026-07-02) — speculative; reliable inputs are RSS/Atom, GDELT, keyed news APIs, Open-Meteo for weather context." ;
    pred:has-phase kb:currents-phase-4 ;
