    <urn:reckons:story/highlight> kb:read-only-guest ;
    <urn:reckons:story/title> "Sharing & Collaboration (Planned)" ;
    <urn:reckons:story/content> "The sharing roadmap progresses through three stages: F2 publishes graphs to GitHub Gist as static TTL files. F3 adds read-only guest views with a Fork button. F4 enables collaborative graphs where guests can propose statements. TTL is the protocol -- no accounts required." .

<urn:reckons:story/rm-step-9>
    <urn:reckons:story/highlight> kb:ent-policy ;
    <urn:reckons:story/content> "The enterprise vision structures organizational knowledge around three dimensions. People: RBAC, team graphs, audit trails. Policy: legal and cultural constraints as graph entities with temporal bounds. Procedure: SOPs and decision trees from intent to execution. Authentication is bring-your-own. Delivery is file-based TTL — portable, diffable, no lock-in." ;
