kb:sveltia-cms-setup
    pred:setup-step "3. Set the worker's GITHUB_CLIENT_ID / GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET vars and ALLOWED_DOMAINS to the OAuth App credentials. ALLOWED_DOMAINS is a comma-separated allowlist (`*` matches one subdomain level); it is 'reckons.ai,*.reckons-ai.pages.dev' so the production custom domain AND the dev branch alias + hashed preview deploys (dev.reckons-ai.pages.dev, <hash>.reckons-ai.pages.dev) can all authenticate. TOOLED — paste the OAuth App's Client ID/Secret into SVELTIA_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID / SVELTIA_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET / SVELTIA_ALLOWED_DOMAINS in .env (see .env.example), then run scripts/sveltia-auth-secrets.sh, which pushes them to the worker via `wrangler secret put`. VERIFIED 2026-07-09: GET /auth?provider=github&site_id=dev.reckons-ai.pages.dev (and a preview hash) both 302 to github.com/login/oauth/authorize; a disallowed domain does not." ;
    pred:description "Wire the /admin content manager. The CMS entry (static/admin/index.html) + config (static/admin/config.yml) ship in the app and are served at Reckons.AI/admin. GitHub login uses sveltia-cms-auth, a small Cloudflare Worker." ;
    pred:setup-step "2. Create a GitHub OAuth App: Settings > Developer settings > OAuth Apps. Homepage https://reckons.ai; Authorization callback URL https://admin.reckons.ai/callback. MANUAL — a human must do this in the GitHub UI." ;
    pred:setup-step "4. backend.base_url in static/admin/config.yml points at https://admin.reckons.ai. DONE." ;
    pred:part-of kb:graph-publishing ;
    pred:setup-step "5. Visit https://reckons.ai/admin/ and Login with GitHub" ;
    pred:alt "Local editing without the worker: Sveltia has no proxy-server backend (@sveltia/cms-proxy-server does not exist on npm) and ignores local_backend (a Decap-only option). On localhost it auto-offers \"Work with Local Repository\" (File System Access API, Chromium-family browsers only) with no config change needed." ;
    rdfs:label "Sveltia CMS — Setup (GitHub OAuth)" ;
    pred:setup-step "1. Deploy sveltia-cms-auth: github.com/sveltia/sveltia-cms-auth (Cloudflare Worker reckons-sveltia-cms-auth, mapped to admin.reckons.ai). DONE." ;
    pred:note "static/admin/index.html now loads a version-pinned Sveltia bundle (@sveltia/cms@0.169.1) instead of an unpinned \"latest\" CDN URL, so upgrades are deliberate. static/media/ (config.yml media_folder) was missing and has been created with a .gitkeep." ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Concept> ;
    pred:note "RESOLVED (2026-07-02): Pages collection listed zero entries after login, even though content/docs/welcome.md and content/releases/v0-1-0.md exist on main with matching frontmatter. Root cause: Sveltia CMS does not implement Decap/Netlify's `nested` collection option at all (confirmed against the pinned @sveltia/cms@0.169.1 bundle and its docs — nested collections are tracked for a future 2.0 release). The committed config's `nested: { depth: 4 }` was silently ignored, so the folder collection fell back to scanning only the immediate content/ directory and found nothing, since both pages live one level down (content/docs/, content/releases/). Fix: replaced `nested: { depth: 4 }` with `path: '{{fields.section | slugify}}/{{fields.slug}}'` in static/admin/config.yml and in the generated-config string sveltiaConfig() in src/lib/publish/site-export.ts (kept in lockstep). `path` is the option Sveltia does support for subfoldered entries: it recursively discovers existing files matching the template and places new ones, with no per-entry index file required. The `slugify` filter mirrors contentPath()'s `slugify(page.section)` so the folder segment matches what's on disk (e.g. section \"Docs\" -> content/docs/). Verified against the real pinned Sveltia bundle via Playwright + the CMS's built-in `test-repo` backend (OPFS-backed, no GitHub auth needed): with the original `nested` config the console logged \"Nested collections are not yet supported in Sveltia CMS\" and the collection showed 0 entries on the exact same seeded files; with the `path` fix it showed 2 entries (Welcome, Reckons.AI v0.1.0) with correct titles/status. Also verified creating a new page (title \"Test Page\", section \"Sandbox\") through the real CMS UI wrote content/sandbox/test-page.md, matching site-export.ts's contentPath() layout exactly. Note: Sveltia's own frontmatter serialization (quoting style, empty-string fields) differs cosmetically from pageToMarkdown()'s canonical form, so scripts/md-align.ts correctly flags freshly CMS-saved files as drifted until they are re-exported from the graph — this is by design, not a bug." ;
    pred:note "/admin is a standalone static page, so the app's strict CSP does not apply; Sveltia reaches api.github.com and the worker directly." ;
    pred:note "RESOLVED (2026-07-02): the earlier bare-404 readiness finding was a missing route — the worker was deployed with the correct sveltia-cms-auth code but had workers.dev previews disabled and no custom domain attached. Fixed by attaching admin.reckons.ai as a Workers custom domain via the Cloudflare API (PUT /accounts/{id}/workers/domains). OAuth App credentials pushed via scripts/sveltia-auth-secrets.sh. Verified: GET /auth?provider=github&site_id=reckons.ai returns 302 to github.com/login/oauth/authorize. Setup steps 1-4 complete; only step 5 (login smoke test at reckons.ai/admin/) remains." .

