    pred:description "Rework the review screen into a full graph workbench: all graph view controls (layout toggles, node search) available on the preview; node details panel on the left with chat below it; the review queue on the right keeps per-item approve/reject/chat actions. Selecting a review item drives the graph (camera fly + selection + name caption + edge highlight). v1 shipped 2026-07-03: clicking an incoming card flies the preview camera to the subject node via the focusKey prop on KnowledgeGraph2D, left-border highlight on the focused card, node-name badge over the graph. v2 shipped 2026-07-03: browse controls (free/focus/hub layout ToggleGroup + a filter-to-highlight node search box) added to the preview's graph pane; a compact node-details panel floats on the left of the graph when a node is selected, showing its label, type, and facts (pending ones tagged), with a scoped chat box below it that seeds the existing Shelly chat (requestShellyChat/TurtleChatPanel) with the node's context rather than a new chat stack; click-to-focus (camera fly + accent border) extended to the deletions, merges, and align tab cards via the same focusStatement path; KnowledgeGraph2D gained an additive highlightedEdges prop that draws the exact incoming triple's edge in bright gold, distinct from the existing orange selection ring. Remaining: none tracked — future polish only (e.g. highlighting the specific edge for deletion/merge suggestions, which aren't currently drawn as graph edges)." ;
