kb:sveltia-edit-mapping
    pred:relates-to kb:change-notes ;
    pred:feature-id "F48" ;
    pred:description "Route CMS commits to the right branch per environment, and map edit KIND to the approval it needs. DONE (per-environment routing, static/admin/index.html): production (reckons.ai and the pages.dev apex) is left to auto-init from config.yml (branch: main) untouched; only the dev branch alias and hashed preview subdomains (*.reckons-ai.pages.dev) take Sveltia manual-init (window.CMS_MANUAL_INIT + CMS.init with load_config_file: true) and override backend.branch to 'dev', so edits made while testing the review flow land on dev, not production main. Verified: the pinned @sveltia/cms@0.169.1 bundle exposes CMS.init and honours CMS_MANUAL_INIT; the host->branch selector is a pure, unit-tested function (reckonsAdminBranch); production path is unchanged. Remaining smoke test: a real dev-login confirms load_config_file merges (collections preserved) and a commit lands on dev. FUTURE: (1) per-content/section mapping (which collections route where); (2) tie edit KIND to approval — trivial human polish self-approves on main (see principle), structural/graph changes flow through F33 gates + F44 change notes; (3) optionally derive the branch from CF_PAGES_BRANCH at build time instead of hostname matching. Relates to F27 publishing, F33 release pipeline, F44 change notes." ;
    pred:has-status "scaffolded" ;
    pred:relates-to kb:release-pipeline ;
    pred:depends-on kb:graph-publishing ;
    pred:principle "Read-only is the default posture for now; editing is opt-in per environment." ;
    rdfs:label "Sveltia Edit Routing & Approval Mapping" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:principle "A small, human, MANUAL markdown polish edit carries its own approval — the human who made the change IS the review. Such edits may commit to main directly without a separate gate. Larger, structural, or graph-shaping changes still go through the F33 review pipeline and F44 change-note approval." ;
    pred:in-dev "2026-07-09"^^xsd:date .

