kb:partial-facts
    pred:in-dev "2026-07-07"^^xsd:date ;
    rdfs:label "Partial Facts & Answer-Flow-Back" ;
    pred:has-status "functional" ;
    pred:feature-id "F32" ;
    pred:depends-on kb:local-model-bench ;
    pred:relates-to kb:review-workbench ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Feature> ;
    pred:description "Human-in-the-loop completion of the F31 local-orchestration loop. When a local sub-agent is uncertain about the OBJECT of a fact it emits a PARTIAL FACT — subject + predicate known, object left as a loose end — together with its question, instead of guessing or spending Opus tokens to resolve it. In the review screen the reviewer FILLS the object rather than editing a guessed value: a search-while-typing picker over existing entities (reusing the RelationBuilder node-list pattern), or create-new (new entity IRI via labelToIri, or a plain text value). Accept is gated until the object is filled. On confirm the resolved fact flows BACK to the waiting sub-agent via knowledge.answers.jsonl in the workspace, so it can resume — closing the loop. Model: Statement gains optional needsObject + question fields (types.ts); pending JSONL lines may omit `object` (carrying a `question`) to denote a partial fact; drainAndImportPending maps these to needsObject statements; kb entityChoices() supplies the picker; workspace recordAnswer() appends the resolved triple to knowledge.answers.jsonl. UI in DiffEntry.svelte. Depends on F31 (Opus + local sub-agents + kb_add_note questions). SHIPPED 2026-07-07: demonstrated end-to-end — local agent hoisted a partial fact (embedding-model quantization ?), human filled it in the review picker as a new entity, the answer flowed back via knowledge.answers.jsonl, and the waiting agent resumed; two bugs found in testing and fixed (computeDiff crashed on placeholder objects; swipe-accept could confirm an unfilled ?)." .

